Ad Text:
Shape the Future of Agribusiness | Drive Data-Led Decisions | Make Regional Impact

 

About Us

We are a well-established lamb and beef processing business located in Bunbury, Western Australia, servicing both domestic and international markets. With deep roots in the regional agricultural economy, our operation is built on operational excellence, sustainability, and end-to-end value-chain optimisation.

Our success is driven by strong partnerships with producers, customers, and the wider supply chain. We are committed to making informed, ethical, and commercially sound decisions that support long-term growth for our business and the communities we operate in.

 

Our Values

INTEGRITY – We do what’s right, even when it’s complex
COLLABORATION – Strong outcomes are built together
CURIOSITY – We seek better ways to operate and improve
ACCOUNTABILITY – We own our decisions and results

 

About the Role

We are seeking a Senior Agribusiness Analyst to join our leadership-facing commercial team at our Bunbury lamb and beef processing facility.

Reporting to the Finance Manager, this influential role partners closely with executive leadership and operations to deliver high-quality commercial insight across the entire red meat value chain.

This is a senior, hands-on role that blends strategic analysis, financial modelling, and operational insight to support profitability, growth, and risk management across livestock procurement, processing, and sales.

 

Key Responsibilities

Lead financial, operational, and market analysis across livestock procurement, processing efficiency, yields, and product margins
Develop and maintain advanced financial models covering pricing, throughput, cost structures, and capital investment scenarios
Analyse lamb and beef market trends, seasonal supply dynamics, and pricing volatility
Partner with operations to identify productivity improvements, yield optimisation, and cost-reduction opportunities
Provide commercial input into budgeting, forecasting, and long-range strategic planning
Support commercial negotiations with producers, agents, and customers through robust data-driven insights
Prepare high-quality reports, dashboards, and presentations for senior leadership and the board
Mentor junior analysts and contribute to continuous improvement of analytical capability, systems, and tools

 

Skills & Experience

Tertiary qualifications in Agribusiness, Finance, Economics, Accounting, or a related discipline
7–10+ years’ experience in agribusiness, food processing, commodities, or a similar commercial environment
Strong understanding of the red meat supply chain (lamb and beef highly desirable)
Advanced financial modelling, forecasting, and data analysis capability
High proficiency in Excel and financial systems; experience with ERP, BI tools, or SQL highly regarded
Strong commercial acumen with the ability to translate complex data into clear, actionable insights
Excellent stakeholder engagement and communication skills, including at executive level

 

Why Join Us

Senior, influential role within a critical regional agribusiness
Competitive remuneration package commensurate with experience
Opportunity to work closely with executive leadership and shape commercial strategy
Relocation support may be considered for the right candidate
Lifestyle benefits of living and working in the Bunbury region

 

Our Benefits:

Competitive Pay: We offer generous pay packages that reward high performers.

Recognition & Rewards: We regularly recognise and reward our people, as well as encouraging employee referrals to our business.

Paid Parental Leave: We provide 13 weeks of paid parental leave on top of NES entitlements.

Health & Well-being: We offer discounted private health insurance and an Employee Assistance Program for you and your immediate household.

Career Growth: We provide opportunities for professional development and career advancement.

Discounted Products: Enjoy premium Pork, Beef and Lamb products at great employee rates.

Exceptional Team Atmosphere: Work in a supportive team where your contribution is valued and success is celebrated.

Income Protection Insurance: Fully subsidised income protection coverage.

Onsite Canteen: Meals, snacks, and beverages available during your workday.

 

Ready to Grow with Us? 

If you're ready to bring your skills and passion to a company that values you, click on apply now to join the Craig Mostyn Group family. Start your rewarding career journey with us today! 

The Craig Mostyn Group is committed to maintaining, growing and supporting our diverse and inclusive culture, by seeking and promoting diversity in our teams. We welcome and encourage applications from people of all ages and genders, and from diverse groups including but not limited to, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, members of the LGBTIQA+ community, people with disabilities and people of all ethnic origins.

Initial contract to commence 23/02/2026 until 07/08/2026 with 12-mth extension option paying $920/day
Brisbane CBD Location with flexibility to WFH 2 days per week
Provide a high level of expertise in establishing and documenting ICT business and system requirements
Our client, Department of Education, are currently seeking a Business Analyst for an initial contract until 07/08/2026 with a likely 12-mth extension.

As the Business Analyst you will have responsibility for the following:

Lead investigative work to determine business requirements and specify effective business processes. Select, adopt and adapt appropriate business analysis methods, tools and techniques, considering business perspectives.
Provide a high level of expertise in establishing and documenting ICT business and system requirements through a range of structured research and analysis techniques including, but not limited to, facilitated stakeholder workshops, surveys, client meetings and industry reference reviews.
Obtain formal agreement from a large and diverse range of potentially senior stakeholders and recipients to the scope and requirements, plus the establishment of a baseline on which delivery of a solution can commence.
Collaborate closely with business and technical stakeholders to ensure requirements are effectively elaborated into prioritised Product Backlog Items (PBIs) and tracked through to business acceptance, supporting direct communication and alignment between stakeholders and the solution development team.
Analyse and design business processes, identify alternative solutions to exploit new technologies and automation, and develop graphical representations of business processes to facilitate understanding and decision making.
Actively support Agile delivery by facilitating timely communication between business and technical teams, ensuring prioritised requirements are updated and aligned with evolving business needs.
Produce conceptual business models in support of business strategy with capability of developing bespoke models for unusual contexts.
Identify the communications and relationship needs of stakeholder groups, translating communications/stakeholder engagement strategies into specific activities and deliverables.
Monitor and share knowledge with other business analyst team members, to contribute to the maintenance of high-quality project deliverables using various management and system design tools.
Undertake research activities in relation to best practice processes and frameworks, new and emerging technologies and organisational development.
Skills and experience required;

Demonstrated well-developed communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills, including the demonstrated experience in conducting workshops, maintaining positive relationships with stakeholders, ICT Operators and other service providers.
Demonstrated experience in identifying and validating multiple requirement types such as Business, systems, configuration and concept and experience modelling business processes using Business Process Modelling Notation (BPMN).
Demonstrated ability to analyse business cases, which define potential benefits, options for achieving these benefits through development of new or change processes and associated business risk
Demonstrated experience and practical understanding of Software Development Lifecycle (SDLC) and PRINCE2 Project Management methodologies. (SDLC & PRINCE2 Methodologies)
To submit your application, in strict confidence, please submit your resume in Word Format using the appropriate link quoting reference No. 248337.  Should you require further information please email kristy.coulter@hudson.com

Your interest will be treated in the strictest of confidence.


Diversity, Equity & Inclusion at Hudson
Hudson is committed to helping you find a workplace where you feel respected, supported, and free to thrive. We welcome applications from all backgrounds, identities, and lived experiences—because when different voices come together, amazing things happen.

Casual Loading 
Please note for all Australian based contract and temporary roles only, the pay rate is inclusive of mandatory 25% casual loading. This excludes permanent and fixed term roles.

About the role (What you’ll be doing)


As the Data Science Lead at Eucalyptus, you’ll lead the development and application of advanced analytics, machine learning, and AI solutions to drive strategic, commercial, and clinical outcomes. You’ll partner closely with Product, Engineering and the broader Data team, to solve high-impact problems, operationalise models, and embed data processes as a core part of the product offering.

In this role, you’ll balance technical leadership and hands-on delivery — setting the vision for how data science is applied while also contributing to complex projects, from sophisticated personalised health insights, to extensive patient context management. You’ll ensure the team’s work is impactful, reliable, and aligned with organisational priorities.

Lead high-impact data science projects: Own the scoping, design, and delivery of models and data context management pipelines that inform highly personalised systems in the technology roadmap.
Guide technical direction: Define the standards, methodologies, and best practices for data science at Eucalyptus, ensuring work is reproducible, explainable, and production-ready.
Collaborate cross-functionally: Partner with stakeholders across the business to translate ambiguous problems into well-defined data science projects with measurable value.
Ensure robust operationalisation: Work with Data Engineering and ML Ops to deploy models, monitor performance, and integrate outputs into products, platforms, and workflows.
Mentor and develop the team: Grow the skills and capabilities of data scientists and analysts through coaching, feedback, and technical guidance.
Stay current: Keep up with established industry practices and emerging methodologies to ensure the team’s work remains effective and relevant.
About you (Who you are)


You’re an experienced data science leader with a proven ability to deliver technically sound, commercially valuable solutions. You balance strategic thinking with hands-on technical work, and you’re skilled at influencing both technical and non-technical audiences.

7+ years of experience in data science, machine learning, or advanced analytics, with at least 2 years in a leadership role.
Proven track record of delivering models and analytics that have driven measurable business or product outcomes.
Strong technical foundation in statistical analysis, machine learning, feature engineering, and model evaluation, and context management for AI systems.
Experience in production environments, working closely with Data Engineering and ML Ops to deploy and monitor models.
Excellent communication skills with the ability to convey technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
Hands-on expertise in SQL, Python, and modern ML/analytics libraries; familiarity with cloud environments (preferably Google Cloud) and tools like BigQuery, Vertex AI, and dbt.
Leadership experience in building, mentoring, and guiding high-performing data science teams.
Passion for applying data and AI to deliver meaningful business and patient outcomes.
Why join Eucalyptus?


Euc is also behind a growing family of digital healthcare clinics (Pilot, Kin, Software, Compound) across men’s health and well-being, fertility, skincare, and preventative health.

Here’s what makes joining Euc unique:

What’s next - Our goal for the next three years is to support 1 million patients globally to live better for longer. We’re launching into new conditions, demographics, and geographies as we build a truly preventive healthcare ecosystem.
Build something world-changing - We’re on the path to becoming the world’s largest international digital healthcare company. It will be challenging, fast-paced, and deeply rewarding.
Make real impact - You will deliver work that directly shapes patient outcomes and scales evidence-based care across markets.
Accelerate your growth - You will have high ownership, continuous feedback, and dedicated development support.
Join a motivated team - You will collaborate with talented peers to solve complex clinical and operational problems at scale.
What’s ahead in Australia?

Grow with us globally - Get mentorship from leaders across Australia, the UK, Germany, and Japan, collaborate with teams in the Philippines and South Africa, and explore new markets or travel internationally. Recognised on Hatch’s Hotlist as one of Australia’s top employers, we support early-career professionals to become future global leaders.
Shape your career - Access learning budgets, conferences, certifications, peer shadowing, and a global knowledge-sharing culture.
Be an owner - Equity for everyone means you share in our success.
Work where well-being matters - Experience catered wellness talks, exercise classes, whoops to track your wellbeing, free barista coffees, funded social clubs, and quarterly rooftop parties.
Innovate with purpose - Use state-of-the-art tools and contribute to bold, impactful solutions in healthcare.
Support at every stage - Benefit from parental and miscarriage leave, to health, professional development, and personal days, Whoop membership, and our Employee Assistance Program.

At Eucalyptus, we value individuals from all backgrounds, experiences, and perspectives, and we embrace the unique qualities each person brings. When you apply, please let us know of any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

Job Title: Data Governance Analyst - 12 Month Max Term Contract
Ad Text:
Opportunity to work with one of the largest General Insurer in Australia

Open to Sydney candidates only - Hybrid opportunity

Play a key role to enhance and execute our Data Governance framework


About Hollard

Hollard Insurance is part of the Hollard Group of Companies and a top 5 General Insurer in Australia and New Zealand. We underwrite a broad range of general insurance products, including motor, home, contents, business, and pet. Hollard’s unrelenting focus on diversity and inclusion, collaborative partnerships, and delivering great customer outcomes is at the heart of its business model, driven by its purpose of “Using our expertise, integrity and humanity to go further, together" 

Your team

You'll be joining the Chief Data Analytics Office (CDAO), who help enable drive data-driven decision making across Hollard. You will be developing its Data Management capability and strenghtening the data foundations for the company. You will be surrounded by data professionals that strive for excellence and drive data best practices to realise business value

Your role

 This role would be a hands-on role combing both your technical experience with Informatica and your love for business engagement.

You will ensure compliance to data standards, correct metadata capturing, support data stewards from the business and establish methods to monitor and report data quality issues. You will manage our corporate metadata to guarantee data classification, data descriptions, business glossary, and data lineage are available and up to date

Your duties and responsibilities

Enhance and execute the enterprise-wide data governance roadmap, ensuring alignment with business priorities and regulatory obligations.

Implement our enterprise AI governance framework that enables the safe, ethical and transparent use of AI/ML technologies across the organisation

Support the integration of Informatica and platforms into enterprise data and AI ecosystems, enabling automation, traceability and auditability.

Help train Data Stewards and Data SMEs on how Informatica can add value to their business in terms of ensuring business glossaries, data dictionary is up to date and data quality rules are in place and issues remediated

Serve as a liaison between Business areas and technology to ensure that Business definitions around data domains are clearly defined and documented

About You

Demonstrated experience in Data Governance projects or implementations.

Strong knowledge or experience with Informatica is highly regarded. 

Strong understanding of data structures and data models is mandatory

Data Risk and Data Strategy experience is highly regarded. 

Intermediate to advanced proficiency in Structured Query Language (SQL) is required

Experience of working in Financial Services or Insurance is a plus.

Strong communication and influencing skills to engage with the business and drive outcomes.

Working at Hollard

At Hollard, you’ll discover an environment where you can truly make an impact. We offer the best of both worlds – the opportunity, agility and creativity of a company growing with scale, alongside a focus on becoming a catalyst for enduring, positive, social change. 

We’re a tight-knit team, where authentic voices and unique perspectives matter. We work supportively, collaboratively and inclusively to help shape our future and create shared value for our communities. 

Hollard proudly promotes flexible work including remote work, non-traditional work patterns, and work-family balance. We’re also unapologetically committed to creating a workplace that values your diversity with a true sense of inclusion.  We actively seek to hire for your different lived experiences, including as it relates to disability, ethnicity, faith, Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, gender diversity, sexual orientation, age, neurodiversity. 

We’re building something special. Working closely with our industry partners to reshape insurance for the better, we’re people changing insurance. 

Please note:  

Even if you don’t meet all our selection criteria, we encourage you to apply.  

A full background check will be completed on the successful applicant. 

Visit the Hollard careers page to learn about how Hollard will collect, store and handle your personal information.  

We are NOT engaging Recruitment Agencies for this role and ask agencies to respect our policy of no unsolicited contact regarding advertised vacancies.

Here's an opportunity to join a large, values-led not-for-profit at a genuinely exciting moment. The organisation is midway through a major, multi-year digitisation program, modernising systems, simplifying processes and reimagining digital experiences so they can better serve their patients and community.

They’re now looking for a Business Analyst who loves working at scale, enjoys untangling complexity, and wants their work to actually make a difference.
 
Contract: 12-month fixed term
 
What you’ll be working on:

This role sits right in the heart of transformation.

Supporting a large-scale digital uplift across systems, processes and user journeys
Partnering with business users, product owners and technical teams to uncover pain points and opportunities
Translating business needs into clear user stories, requirements, process flows and solution designs
Contributing to solution options, roadmaps and business cases
Working across enterprise platforms such as MS Dynamics (or similar CRM / ERP / HRIS systems)
Supporting delivery teams through backlog refinement, testing and change readiness
About you

You’re a confident, curious BA who enjoys bringing structure to ambiguity and clarity to complex environments. You’re comfortable working across multiple stakeholder groups and don’t shy away from enterprise-scale change.

You’ll bring:

3+ years’ experience as a Business Analyst in digital, enterprise or technology-focused environments
Strong understanding of human-centred design principles
Exposure to MS Dynamics or similar CRM / ERP / HRIS platforms
Strong analysis, documentation and stakeholder engagement skills
The ability to adapt in a fast-moving, evolving program
Clear communication and a genuine commitment to quality outcomes
Why join? 

Be part of a purpose-driven NFP making a meaningful community impact
Contribute to a significant digital transformation that will shape future service delivery
Supportive, collaborative and down-to-earth culture
Package of $140,000 - $150,000 + salary packaging benefits
Flexible working + hybrid model (3 days in the office)
Richmond location, close to transport and great coffee 
What happens next?

If this sounds like you, don’t wait - applications are encouraged ASAP.

If you have questions please reach out to Jamie on jamie@frazertremble.com.au

We’ve been proudly serving Australian communities since 1914 and have grown to become a top 30-listed company on the ASX with a portfolio of iconic homegrown brands. At the heart of our continued success is over 115,000 team members working across the country, all contributing to bringing our customers smiles. You’ll not only get to see your work make a difference, you’ll be part of a team working together to help Australians eat and live better every day.

 

About the team

 

Our Technology team is the backbone of the business, building and maintaining the information technology infrastructure that support Coles Group. As a part of the Technology team, you get the opportunity to work through complex, challenging, meaningful problems using large data sets and new technologies to expand your skills and experience.




 

Primary Responsibilities

 

Responsible for an enterprise wide analysis to understand the problem and define the solution for platform engineering
Investigates problems and analyses options for new and existing platform services, providing recommendations to solutions and produces artefacts such as domain models, workflows, user stories and interface design
Facilitate collaboration and lead effective communication with all stakeholders to support design, build and delivery to meet the user needs for cloud products being engineered
Able to analyse current services and processes, and then identify and implement opportunities to optimise these
Confident working with back-end systems, microservices, databases etc, and actively drive the gap analysis, data mapping and future state of these systems
Work in close collaboration with the Product Manager and Engineering Manager is maturing the product roadmap

 

 

Experience

 

Accurately describe the problem statement, business impact and the technology solution approach
Ability to facilitate and run workshops, showcases and other ceremonies to support product technology and product engineering activities (e.g. discovery, event storming, goal settings)
Responsible for elicitation of engineering requirements, including writing user stories for agile teams
Works with stakeholders to prioritise the product backlog based on value and timelines
Collaborates with the team members to ensure the outcomes match the project requirements and meet the quality standards
Has a solid understanding of ‘systems of work’ (agile, non-agile, SDLC, CD), and is able to identify areas for improvement and drive change
Helps to evaluate and clarify requirements requirement gaps, and resolve conflicting or ambiguous requirements

 

 

Commercial Skills & Qualifications

 

Appropriate tertiary and/or industry experience
Strong understanding of Agile development
Excellent written & verbal communication skills
Hands on experience working in complex technology environments using multiple delivery frameworks
Understanding of contemporary integration patterns and techniques in cloud (Azure, AWS or Google); and · Experience working with microservices in a cloud environment

 



What’s in it for you?

 

Flexible working options: We know that work is only one part of your life, so we actively encourage a positive work-life balance and provide hybrid working options to help you achieve it.
Office perks: Take advantage of our gym facility and fitness classes, free parking, BBQ area, mini-Coles supermarket, fooderie hub where you can sample new products before they hit the shelves, school holiday program and so much more when you come in.
Discounts: Eligible team members receive 5% discount all year round on your Supermarket and Liquor online and in-store purchases. We also offer additional periods of double discount (10%) at various times throughout the year. As well as hotdeals exclusive to team members that translate into additional savings.
Reward through recognition: Give and receive recognition, linked to our Coles values, through our digital recognition platform ‘mythanks’. You can accumulate points to redeem in the online shop for exciting gifts and electronic gift cards from an extensive range of retailers.
Opportunities for learning and development: No matter where you start within our diverse business, you’ll have experiences, exposure, and education to satisfy you. Discover and explore a variety of career development programs and job-specific training.
Paid parental leave: We understand how important your life outside work is and offer permanent team members paid parental leave to support you in balancing work and family.
Investment in your future: Our annual team member share plan offer allows eligible team members to make regular pre-tax salary sacrifice deductions to purchase Coles Group shares.

 

About the recruitment process

 

We’re continuing to build a gender equitable team, and a culture that is just as diverse, inclusive and welcoming as the communities we serve. We are committed to creating a workplace that is safe and respectful for our team. We encourage applications from people of all ages, cultures (including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples), abilities, sexual orientation and gender identities.

 

We’re happy to adjust our recruitment process to support candidates with disability. For further information and additional contact details visit the ‘Our Recruitment Process’ section of our careers site or email inclusionrecruitment@coles.com.au

Job Title: Senior Strategy and Continuous Improvement Specialist
Category:
Strategy & Planning (Consulting & Strategy)
Government - Federal (Government & Defence)
Ad Text:
Shape enterprise strategy at one of Australia's most iconic institutions

Newly created permanent position

Sydney-based hybrid work environment



About the team

The Enterprise Strategy and Change Department enables the Reserve Bank of Australia to deliver on its Corporate Plan by coordinating enterprise strategic planning, governing the enterprise project portfolio, delivering IT-enabled change, and embedding a continuous improvement capability.

As part of this department, the Strategy & Continuous Improvement team plays a central role in shaping the Bank's strategic direction and driving operational excellence. This newly created role will report to the Manager - Continuous Improvement, and work closely with the Manager - Strategic Planning to support enterprise-wide initiatives. While the primary focus is on enterprise continuous improvement, the role will flex to support strategic planning and execution efforts as needed, ensuring balanced delivery across the broader team.

About the role

As a Senior Strategy and Continuous Improvement Specialist (Continuous Improvement Focus), you will:


Lead enterprise continuous improvement capability development, partnering with senior leaders and business units to shape and execute enterprise-wide continuous improvement initiatives, embed improvement practices that enhance efficiency and effectiveness, while aligning with the Bank's strategic priorities.

Design and evolve the Bank's enterprise CI frameworks and systems, ensuring robust governance, performance alignment, and integration with strategic planning processes.

Conduct structured analysis and process reviews to identify improvement opportunities, validate hypotheses, and inform decisions that support both operational excellence and strategic outcomes.

Facilitate CI workshops, problem-solving sessions, and capability uplift programs across the organisation to build a culture of continuous improvement that complements strategic objectives.

Develop innovative CI solutions to address complex organisational challenges, ensuring they deliver measurable impact and support long-term strategic direction.

Collaborate with the enterprise strategy team as needed to ensure improvement initiatives are prioritised and aligned with enterprise strategy.

Engage executives, committees, and governance bodies through clear communication and compelling storytelling that demonstrates the value of CI in achieving strategic goals.

Help build a high-performing, values-led CI function that drives operational excellence, fosters alignment, and amplifies enterprise impact.

About you

You are a collaborative problem solver and continuous improvement champion with a passion for driving operational excellence and meaningful change. You bring:

Experience & Expertise


6 to 8+ years' experience in continuous improvement, process optimisation, and transformation within large, complex institutions, with exposure to strategic alignment.

Minimum 3 years in strategy / management consulting role at Manager level or equivalent (e.g. Big Four, Tier 1.5, MBB); strong consulting toolkit.

Experience in financial services or public sector environments (highly regarded).

Strong analytical and stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to shape enterprise CI frameworks, apply proven methodologies, map processes, identify improvement opportunities, and design performance and benefit realisation models that quantify, forecast, and link initiatives to strategic outcomes.

Experience designing and applying organisational value chains to identify improvement opportunities, drive measurable benefits, and enable strategic impact at scale.

Proven ability to translate improvement opportunities into actionable plans and measurable benefits, aligned with enterprise strategy.

Experience supporting executive-level engagements and enterprise-wide improvement initiatives, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities.

Skills & Capabilities


Proficient at synthesising a variety of information and data into insights, options, and recommendations.

Excellent communication skills (verbal, written, and visual) with the ability to influence and engage across all levels.

Strong workshop design and facilitation skills (e.g. strategy co-design, strategic planning, process mapping/improvement, capability uplift).

Ability to work autonomously and collaboratively in a high-performing team.

Comfortable navigating ambiguity, learning and adapting quickly, and delivering results in a dynamic environment.

Understanding of financial services regulation, compliance, and institutional accountability (highly regarded).

Qualifications


Tertiary qualifications in Business, Finance, Economics, Engineering, or a related discipline.

Postgraduate qualifications, e.g. MBA (highly regarded).

Certifications in Human-Centred Design, Design Thinking, Agile, Lean Six Sigma, or Project/Program Management (e.g. PRINCE2, MSP, PMI) are advantageous but not mandatory.

Why Join Us


Purpose-driven work that shapes the prosperity of Australia.

Opportunity to influence enterprise-wide strategy and transformation in a unique central bank context.

Collaborative, high-integrity culture that values excellence, learning, and inclusion.

Hybrid working model with flexibility to work from home and the office, as agreed with your manager


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people. Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward. Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

Join a culture of success

Work alongside a talented CFO to shape the FP&A function

Take on a pivotal role working closely with multiple stakeholders in this large construction business

Sydney CBD, $130K - $150K Package (experience dependent)

Company Background

Our client is a large, well-established construction company with a strong footprint across Australia and continuing expansion overseas. Known for delivering high-quality, large-scale, major projects and operating with a long-term, sustainable approach, the business is continuing to expand its portfolio worldwide.

As part of this growth, they are seeking a Financial Analyst to join the team and play a key role alongside the CFO in shaping the global FP&A function. You will join a highly professional, collaborative environment where excellence, accountability, and continuous improvement are part of the culture.

The Role

Your remit as Financial Analyst will be appealingly broad, encompassing a range of responsibilities including, but not limited to, the following:

Annual budgeting, rolling forecasts, and long-range financial planning across regions and projects

Analyse project performance, including cost-to-complete, margin, cash flow, and variance to budget/forecast

Deliver monthly management reporting with clear insights on project, regional, and group performance

Partner with operations and project teams to support financial decision-making and improve profitability

Drive improvements in FP&A systems, reporting, and forecasting processes

Your Background

To be considered for this Financial Analyst role, you will be a qualified or part-qualified Accountant (e.g. CA, CPA, ACCA, CIMA or equivalent) and will meet most of the following criteria:

Proven experience in budgeting, forecasting and analysis

Industry experience is not a prerequisite; however, any relevant industry experience is welcome

An excellent attitude

Outstanding written and verbal communication skills to work as an effective finance business partner

Those working as a Management Accountant or Senior Accountant with at least a couple of years of Analytical experience are welcome to apply.

If you are keen to apply for this Financial Analyst role, please contact Cass Pratt at Richard Lloyd on 02 8324 2014, quoting reference 9796 or click on 'apply now' below.

Please submit your CV in Word format and note that due to the high volume of responses we receive only suitable candidates will be contacted.

Company description:



When you choose AusNet, you'll join genuine people working together, making Real. Progress

At AusNet, we're the link between renewable energy sources and local communities, playing a vital role in Australia's clean energy transition. Here, your work creates meaningful impact for millions of Victorians.



Job description:



And right now — Strategy is the place to be!

This is our third Strategy Lead vacancy due to rapid business growth. If you're looking for a team where your potential is recognised and your pathway is fast‑tracked, this is your moment.

Purposeful work with genuinely good people. That's refreshing.

We have an opportunity for a Strategy Lead to deliver high‑quality insights and strategic recommendations that shape the direction of our Transmission business, influence executive decision‑making, and support the once‑in‑a‑generation energy transition.

This role is based at Freshwater Place and sits within our Transmission Strategy & Regulation team.

This role will deliver real outcomes, including but not limited to:

Solving complex, ambiguous problems across network planning, asset strategy and long‑term transmission outlooks
Leading strategic deep dives and developing insights that guide Board and Executive decision‑making
Supporting long‑term strategic agenda development for Transmission
Simplifying complex technical topics into compelling, executive‑ready narratives

You don't need to check every box; however, we are looking for someone with a strong consulting tool kit and a good combination of:

Strategic consulting experience gained in a top‑tier or highly regarded strategy firm environment, with 2-3+ years working on complex, ambiguous, business‑critical problems.
Exceptional structured problem‑solving capability — able to rapidly break down complex issues, analyse data and develop clear, actionable insights.
Outstanding written and verbal communication skills, including executive‑ready PowerPoint storytelling and the ability to simplify technical concepts.
Strong stakeholder engagement skills — confident extracting insights from SMEs, influencing senior leaders, and presenting to Board‑level audiences.

A real place to belong

You'll join a collaborative, highly trusted Strategy team that acts as a true advisor to the business. We work with integrity, care for one another, and champion diverse perspectives.

We believe in more than just competitive pay. Here's what sets us apart:

Development: Strategy is a proven incubator — the strategy team is highly regarded by the organisation and viewed as an accelerator for future leaders
Flexibility: Hybrid work, flexible hours, and space to balance life.
Leave: Generous personal leave and 14 weeks paid parental leave (no minimum service).
Community Giving: Paid volunteer days with Foodbank or your chosen cause.
Perks: Purchased leave, income protection, novated leasing and corporate discounts.

Join a team shaping Victoria's energy future.

Job Title: Senior Analyst - Strategic Intelligence - Cyber Intelligence
Ad Text:
We are looking for a Senior Analyst to join the strategic intelligence capability within CyberCX Intelligence. Be part of a dynamic, high-performing team with unparalleled visibility into our region's cyber threat landscape. Our ideal candidate will value a highly collegiate environment, have excellent analysis and writing skills, and be ready to run an intelligence desk focussed on key sectors or geographies.
  
About the team
CyberCX Intelligence is a dedicated intelligence capability, with experts in tactical, operational and strategic intelligence. Situated inside one of the world’s largest end-to-end cyber security companies, we have the information, access and context to help our customers to make better decisions at all levels: from cyber defence teams to Boardrooms.
  
How you’ll make an impact
As a Senior Analyst, you will inform and shape the decisions of security and business leaders in Australia and globally. You will provide real-time intelligence support to high-profile cyber incidents and generate well-researched intelligence reports that help our customers understand their cyber threat profile, and what they can do about it.

Day to day you will:

Monitor the global and regional threat landscape to identify and action threat information and to develop subject matter expertise across particular sectors and/or geographies.
Manage a portfolio of customer relationships, prepare and disseminate intelligence in a timely and actionable manner, and elicit feedback on intelligence products.
Identify intelligence collection priorities for diverse customers, identify and improve collection sources, and mobilise a diverse team to meet priorities through daily intelligence collection activities.
Collect and synthesise information from multiple sources and use analytic techniques to validate, prioritise and contextualise information relevant to your portfolio and customers.
Write short form intelligence SITREPs and advisories, often under time pressure, for cyber practitioners and longer form intelligence reports for business leaders.
Lead, coach and mentor Associate Analysts and Analysts from diverse backgrounds and with diverse skillsets.
Key skills and attributes

Excellent analytical and problem-solving skills with a demonstrated ability to analyse and amalgamate diverse information to deliver results
Excellent communication skills, with the ability to produce oral and written products with structure, clarity and precision
Strong stakeholder engagement and project management skills and a track record of delivering results in high-pressure environments
Developed understanding of the region’s cyber threat landscape.
Experience and qualifications

At least 5 years’ relevant professional experience, with experience in intelligence and consulting both highly regarded.
Fluency in the intelligence lifecycle, analytic techniques, and open source intelligence.
Familiarity with common cyber threat intelligence frameworks like MITRE ATT&CK, Diamond Model or Cyber Kill Chain.
Minimum Bachelor’s degree.
What's in it for you?

Flexible working in a hybrid arrangement (a blend of office and WFH).
A high-performing, collegiate team with a commitment to continuous learning.
A dynamic environment where no day is the same, and you make a difference to customers and communities.
Once-in-a-career growth opportunities.
Attractive salary and employee benefits package.

Company Description

With roots dating back to 1913, ALDI is proud to make a real difference to people across the world by offering top quality products for low prices. ALDI first entered the Australian grocery market in 2001 and has since grown to have almost 600 stores and 8 distribution centres in 5 states.

If you’ve ever shopped at ALDI you know we are not your average supermarket.  We’re also not your average employer. ALDI is a place where you’ll find good people, good purpose and great opportunities. So, you can work with a great team, feel great for making a real difference for everyday Australians and enjoy a rewarding career.

It’s that simple. ALDI Good Different.

Job Description

We are seeking a strategic Analyst to join our Forecasting and Data Analytics team and be a driving force in improving our execution of replenishment through data driven decisions. This role is a permanent full-time position, based in Minchinbury.

Join a team that values your contribution and provides opportunities for continuous learning to develop into a supply chain expert. You will embrace a growth mindset, eager to shape the future of supply chain excellence by elevating the replenishment process and directly contribute to ALDI's strategic goals.

What does the role look like? 

Extract and analyse large data sets to identify key insights that drive business decisions across ALDI's supply chain.
Develop data driven solutions to complex challenges and enhancing forecasting accuracy.
Build, test, and deploy machine learning models using Python, SQL and R to solve problems in forecasting, operations, and automation.
Visualise data by creating and maintaining meaningful reports and dashboards using Power Bi.
Consolidate multiple data sources and analysing patterns, trends, anomalies, and root causes.
Identify opportunities for improvement within the entire supply chain and providing actionable insights.

And the best part? Every single day at ALDI, you'll know you're making a difference, supporting our mission to help everyday Australians live richer lives for less.

Qualifications
Demonstrated data analysis experience with statistical analysis techniques using relevant software (e.g., R, Python, SQL).
Knowledge in statistics, machine learning, and optimisation methods for experimentation and operational decision-making.
Ability to leverage data-driven insights to inform and drive strategic decision-making within a dynamic business environment.
Experience in forecasting/demand planning within an FMCG environment highly regarded.
Experience in SAP forecasting modules and data visualisation tools is an advantage.
Experience in the data science lifecycle, including development and deployment highly regarded.
Additional Information
Enjoy 5 weeks annual leave for pursuing your passions outside of work.
Enjoy the flexibility of hybrid work options.
Support during life’s most important moments including paid parental leave, including superannuation on parental leave.
Complimentary access to free physiotherapy to treat non-work-related aches, pains or niggles.
Work with a company who has been recognised as an Employer of Choice every year since 2018 - 2024.
Boost your wellbeing with the MyALDI wellbeing program with discounted access to Fitness Passport and health insurance.

Remuneration

Transparent tiered salary range of $143,400 - $163,500 including Superannuation.

Ready to embark on a good different career? To learn more about what it is like to work at ALDI visit our careers website www.aldicareers.com.au

St Vincent's Health Australia is a national leader in compassionate, innovative healthcare. Our Virtual & Home division (SVVH) is transforming how care is delivered, using digital innovation and home-based models to create a more connected and equitable health system.

As the Business Analyst, you will support the design, development and optimisation of digital health and service delivery initiatives.

You will work closely with clinical, operational, technical and executive stakeholders to analyse demand, translate complex data into actionable insights, and support scalable, sustainable models of care.

You will play a critical part in enabling data-driven decision-making, supporting digital health innovation, and improving patient outcomes through insight-led service design.

Key Responsibilities


Elicit, analyse and document business and user requirements for digital health initiatives.
Analyse operational, clinical and financial data to identify trends, gaps and opportunities.
Develop dashboards, reports and insights to support decision-making and performance monitoring.
Research population demand, demographics, geography and funding impacts.
Map and improve workflows and processes to enhance efficiency and patient experience.
Support innovation through AI, automation and digital health solutions.
Facilitate workshops, interviews and user journey mapping sessions.
Maintain high-quality documentation including business cases, requirements and process maps.
Support governance, reporting, risk management and benefits realisation activities.


About You
Essential


Demonstrated experience as a Business Analyst (healthcare, digital health or service design preferred).
Strong analytical, problem-solving and data interpretation skills.
Experience in requirements gathering, process mapping and stakeholder engagement.
Proficiency in data visualisation and reporting tools (e.g. Power BI, Tableau).
Excellent communication, facilitation and documentation skills.
Ability to work in agile, cross-functional teams.

Desirable


Experience in virtual care, aged care or health service delivery.
Familiarity with human-centred design and co-design approaches.
Understanding of healthcare funding, regulation and digital health standards.
Experience in not-for-profit or mission-led organisations.


Qualifications


Tertiary qualifications in business, marketing, health administration or a related field.


Why St Vincent's?
Care for each other -as well as the people we serve - underpins everything we do at St Vincent's. Guided by our values of compassion, excellence, integrity and justice, we promote a culture of diversity and inclusion and empower our people to learn, grow and innovate.

We strive to ensure all our people feel supported, valued and safe every day they come to work with us.

When you join the St Vincent's family, you will have access to:


Growth & development: Access ongoing learning, professional development and industry-leading educational partnerships across NSW, VIC and QLD.
Salary sacrifice: As a not-for-profit provider, we offer generous salary packaging - enabling part of your salary to be taken home tax-free, including access to a meal-entitlement card.
Discounts, health and wellbeing: Access a range of employee perks including discounted gym memberships and our free 24/7 staff counselling and wellbeing service.
Workplace giving: Opportunities to engage in volunteering and community programs, including paid volunteering leave and workplace giving initiatives.

This is your opportunity
Shape the future of virtual care in Australia -designing solutions that enable people to live well, with dignity, connection and choice.

Ready to Apply?
If you're driven by purpose, excited by digital care innovation and motivated to build something extraordinary, we'd love to hear from you.

Apply today and help us deliver care that is compassionate, connected, and life changing. Please submit your current CV along with a cover letter.

We will be assessing applications as they are received and may close the advert earlier than the listed closing date.

Because you're like us, you believe in our vision that every person, whoever and wherever they are, is served with excellent and compassionate care, by a better and fairer health and aged care system. Better for all our employees and volunteers, who work tirelessly to provide the highest levels of care and quality of life for our patients and clients. And better support for the local communities we play a vital role in and continue to support.

Pre-Employment Checks
Your employment is conditional upon the completion of all role-required pre-employment checks, including relevant immunisations.

Equal Opportunity
We celebrate diversity & inclusion and are committed to equal employment opportunity for everyone. This affirmative action allows a specific position within St Vincent's to be available exclusively to Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander individuals.

Support the development of service offerings that strengthen NCVER's impact and reputation.

Ensure a strong focus on analytical rigor, continuous improvement and customer experience.

Lead, coach, and develop a multidisciplinary team of data analysts, researchers and information services professionals.

With roots dating back to 1913, ALDI is proud to make a real difference to people across the world by offering top quality products for low prices. ALDI first entered the Australian grocery market in 2001 and has since grown to have almost 600 stores and 8 distribution centres in 5 states.

If you’ve ever shopped at ALDI you know we are not your average supermarket.  We’re also not your average employer. So, you can work with a great team, feel great for making a real difference for everyday Australians and enjoy a rewarding career.

It’s that simple. ALDI Good Different.

Job Description

Join a highly impactful team as a Strategy Analyst (Storytelling) in the Financial Planning and Analysis (FP&A) department of ALDI Stores, based in Minchinbury. This is a 12-month contract opportunity.

This role sits at the intersection of strategy, finance, retail insight, and visual storytelling. The core job is turning complex commercial analysis into clear, structured, visually appealing narratives that are executive ready. You will have the opportunity to leave a lasting imprint on the business and influence our success.

What does the role involve?   

Develop polished, board-ready presentations and documents, featuring executive briefing notes, structured logic, and visually impactful layouts.
Translate complex datasets from multiple sources, financial models, and analyses into actionable insights, risks and opportunities to executive leaders.
Design process maps, frameworks, timelines, decision trees, and conceptual diagrams to visualise information clearly.
Apply consulting best practice frameworks using problem statements, hypothesis-led thinking, evaluation of options, implications, and recommendations to optimise commercial outcomes.
Collaborate closely with finance, strategy, and operational stakeholders to provide financial support on business strategy and ensure messaging is tailored and effective for CFO, CEO, and Board-level communications.

And the best part? Every single day at ALDI, you'll know you're making a difference, supporting our mission to help everyday Australians live richer lives for less.

Qualifications
Demonstrated experience within a commercial finance, consulting, business analysis environment or similar highly regarded.
Background in Big 4, strategy consulting, internal strategy, or PMO highly regarded.
Proven demonstrated experience of financial planning and analysis.
Proven organisational skills, attention to detail and ability to work under pressure (independently without supervision and in a team environment).
Strong interpersonal and relationship building skills with the ability to clearly and effectively communicate to executive board stakeholders.
Proficiency in utilising various reporting tools to analyse data- such as Excel, Think-Cell, Power Bi or Tableau.
Additional Information
Enjoy 5 weeks annual leave for pursuing your passions outside of work.
Enjoy the flexibility of hybrid work options.
Support during life’s most important moments including paid parental leave, including superannuation on parental leave.
Complimentary access to free physiotherapy to treat non-work related aches, pains or niggles.
Work with a company who has been recognised as an Employer of Choice every year since 2018 - 2024.
Boost your wellbeing with the MyALDI wellbeing program with discounted access to Fitness Passport and health insurance.

Remuneration:

Transparent tiered salary range of $143,400 - $163,500 including Superannuation.

Process Improvement Specialist




Are you ready to make a real impact in Australia’s energy transition?




At AusNet, we play a key role in the energy transition and provide essential energy to Victorian households and businesses.




Help us lead the way, while enriching your career with real people who encourage you to bring your best and make real impact – for your career, our communities and Australia’s clean energy future.







About the role




The Process Improvement Specialist drives enterprise‑wide process excellence by facilitating stakeholder workshops, mapping processes from level 1 to 5, uncovering inefficiencies, and leading improvement initiatives that support safe, reliable, and efficient energy services. You will coach process owners and stewards to build capability and embed a culture of continuous improvement using Lean, Six Sigma, and Kaizen.


You will leverage business process management tools to model and mine processes, extract insights, and visualise real‑time flows to identify deviations, bottlenecks, and performance gaps, supporting workflow redesign, automation, and best‑practice implementation.


The role supports the enterprise process management framework by ensuring processes are mapped, well‑documented, version‑controlled, and accessible for training, audits, and ongoing improvement. By strengthening end‑to‑end processes and regulatory readiness, the Process Improvement Specialist helps embed operational excellence that drives performance, innovation, and resilience.







Key Responsibilities




Support the enterprise process framework and tools by driving implementation, adoption, and continuous improvement, ensuring processes are mapped, documented, optimised, and aligned with enterprise standards and best practices.

Facilitate cross‑functional workshops with frontline staff, SMEs, and leadership to map current‑state processes, identify pain points, co‑design future‑state improvements, and build process ownership across functions.

Lead enterprise‑wide improvement initiatives across Gas Operations, Electricity Distribution, Transmission, Digital, Future Networks, Group Operations and Corporate Functions to improve safety, efficiency, reliability, compliance, and customer service.

Conduct end‑to‑end diagnostics of operational and support processes to identify inefficiencies, waste, duplication, and bottlenecks using Lean, Six Sigma, and value stream mapping.

Standardise and document critical processes in line with AusNet’s Integrated Management System (IMS), regulatory requirements, and operational risk frameworks.

Partner with leaders and technical specialists to translate strategic objectives into operational workflows and continuous improvement initiatives that deliver measurable performance uplift.

Collaborate with Data & Analytics and Digital Enablement to develop dashboards, KPIs, and real‑time visualisation tools that support decision‑making and process monitoring.

Embed continuous improvement capability by coaching team leaders, field supervisors, and support staff in CI tools, root‑cause analysis, visual management, and standard work.

Support transformation and change programs, including process re‑engineering for new systems, organisational shifts, and major capital project delivery.

Ensure operational processes meet compliance obligations, including safety, environmental performance, regulator reporting (AER, ESV), and critical infrastructure risk management.

Capture lessons learned from incidents, audits, and emergency management exercises and integrate them into sustainable improvements and training materials.

Lead process maturity assessments across business units and contribute to the enterprise Operational Excellence maturity roadmap and reporting cadence.

Drive cross‑business process harmonisation by identifying and resolving variation that impacts performance, regulatory alignment, or scalability across regulated networks and Future Networks developments. 







What You’ll Bring

You bring advanced facilitation and workshop leadership skills, engaging stakeholders from field teams to executives. You have strong process mapping, problem‑solving, and analytical skills using BPM tools, Confluence, or similar.




You coach others in CI tools, build local capability, and communicate complex process issues clearly. You are proficient in root cause analysis, standard work design, and process documentation, and you manage multiple initiatives concurrently while delivering outcomes in fast‑paced or ambiguous environments.




 

Qualifications:

Tertiary qualification in Engineering, Operations Management, Business, or a related discipline.

Certified in Lean Six Sigma (minimum Green Belt required; Black Belt desirable).

Formal training in continuous improvement, change management, or operational excellence methodologies (e.g. Kaizen, A3 thinking, root cause analysis).

Familiarity with ISO standards and integrated management systems (e.g. ISO 9001, ISO 55001) is advantageous.







 

Skills:

5+ years' experience in process improvement and operational excellence.

Skilled in facilitating cross-functional workshops to map current state, co-design future state, and foster ownership. 

Experienced in coaching individuals and teams on process management and continuous improvement.

Demonstrated experience leading end-to-end improvement projects with measurable business outcomes.

Proven track record in embedding sustainable process change and building capability at team level.

Strong understanding of continuous improvement methodologies such as Lean, Six Sigma, Kaizen, and value stream mapping.

Knowledge of operational processes within asset-intensive, safety-critical, or regulated environments (e.g. energy, utilities, infrastructure).

Familiarity with integrated management systems (IMS), ISO standards (e.g. ISO 9001, ISO 55001), and regulatory compliance frameworks.

Awareness of key business functions including field operations, emergency management, asset management, safety, and capital delivery.







Please note, we will not be engaging in Recruitment agencies for this role, please apply directly!

 

 

 

A real place to belong.




We celebrate unique voices, refreshing perspectives and diversity in our team. Engage and connect through our social club, wide range of events or by joining one of our Employee Network Groups.




We believe in more than just competitive pay. Here’s what sets us apart:

Leave: more than typical personal leave and a generous 14 weeks of paid parental leave, with no minimum service.

Community giving: a paid day to volunteer with our social impact partner, Foodbank, or for a cause that matters to you.

Perks: we offer all the other perks you’ve come to expect like purchased leave, income protection insurance, novated leasing, corporate discounts, private health cover discounts and more.




As an industry in transformation, we’re excited by the possibilities ahead.

So, if you’re passionate about our purpose and committed to making real progress, bring your energy and join AusNet. Together, we can shape a new way forward.

About the Role:

As a Business Analyst, you will work with stakeholders from all parts of BaptistCare to elicit requirements and capture business needs, to articulate and document business requirements, to conduct as-is/to-be business process mapping and business process design, to participate in project delivery through design reviews and walk-throughs, to validate and communicate outcomes.

Step into a high-impact role at the heart of a major acquisition. As our Business Analyst, you’ll play a pivotal role in transitioning and integrating the acquisition of 10 Retirement Villages into our broader WA operations. You’ll lead the charge in consolidating and migrating critical data, ensuring a smooth, well-orchestrated transition from day one.

You’ll dive deep into end-to-end business processes; from sales, bonds and admissions through to payroll, accounts payable, onboarding and aged debtors—capturing the workflows, system processes and business rules that keep operations running.

By comparing incumbent processes with BaptistCare’s ways of working, you’ll uncover gaps, overlaps and opportunities for improvement, helping shape a stronger, more streamlined future state. You’ll also be central to migration planning, bringing clarity to priorities, sequencing and dependencies to keep this complex transition on track.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead the documentation of current-state business processes associated with the data entry onto systems, document the integrations, data flows and storage locations.
Map end-to-end workflows and system processes, capturing key business rules and operational dependencies.
lead a comparison analysis of processes and data to identify gaps, overlaps and improvement opportunities in Baptistcare’s systems.
Define the migration approach to BaptistCare’s core systems, including but not limited to Epicor, TechOne, MS Dynamics, Salesforce).
Identify and prioritise capability uplift and system enhancements to support the acquisition and future-state design.
Support transition planning by clarifying priorities, sequencing and dependencies to ensure a smooth integration.

About the Team:

The Information & Digital team drives innovation and transforms care at BaptistCare through cutting-edge technology, seamless operations, and smart risk management. You’ll join a collaborative, solutions-focused team that values creativity, flexibility, and turning complex projects into real-world impact for our frontline teams..

About You:

Minimum 5 years’ experience as a business analyst delivering complex process, data and system change initiatives.
Demonstrated experience working on enterprise system implementations or replacements, particularly finance, payroll, CRM or care-related platforms.
Tertiary qualification in Business, Information Technology, Business Analysis or a related discipline.
Experience in mapping, analysing, and improving business processes using BPMN or other structured process methodologies.
Solid understanding of systems, data and integration concepts, with the ability to document application and data architectures.
Experience defining and supporting data and system migration approaches, including sequencing, dependencies and risk considerations.
High-level written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate complex concepts for executives, business users and technical team
Previous experience participating on Project teams
Experience using business analysis and delivery tools such as Visio, Jira, Confluence, MS Project or equivalent.
Ability to develop relationships with key organisational stakeholders, including Execs and Business users.
Highly developed interpersonal skills and ability to work harmoniously in a team environment.

Desirable experience includes:

Experience in acquisitions, transitions or large-scale migrations, ideally involving multi-system environments, highly desirable
Experience with Healthcare and Aged Care systems and technology
Experience with Project Management

As a for purpose, Christian care organisation, we are committed to providing exceptional support and services across Australia.  Together with Baptcare (VIC, TAS, SA) and Baptist Care SA we employ over 12,000 dedicated employees and support over 38,000 customers to help people live well with dignity and purpose. Join us on our mission to make a better world of work. 

Culture Amp is the world’s leading employee experience platform, revolutionizing how 25 million employees across more than 6,500 companies create a better world of work. Culture Amp empowers companies of all sizes and industries to transform employee engagement, drive performance management, and develop high-performing teams. Powered by people science and the most comprehensive employee dataset in the world, the most innovative companies including Canva, On, Asana, Dolby, McDonalds and Nasdaq depend on Culture Amp every day.

Culture Amp is backed by leading venture capital funds and has offices in the US, UK, Germany and Australia. Culture Amp has been recognized as one of the world’s top private cloud companies by Forbes and most innovative companies by Fast Company.

For more information visit cultureamp.com.

How you can help make a better world of work

We're looking for a Senior Engineer to join the AI Research & Experience team, helping build AI Coach - Culture Amp's contextually-aware AI system that integrates survey insights, performance management, and interpersonal dynamics to deliver personalized support to organizations, teams, and individuals at scale.

You'll work at the intersection of applied AI research and product engineering, translating cutting-edge techniques into production systems that genuinely improve how people experience work. This isn't a research lab - you'll be shipping features that solve real customer problems. 

What you'll do

Staying up to date with current research, literature and provider offerings. 
Design, implement and evaluate areas and features of our multi-agentic platform and systems using modern frameworks (e.g., LangGraph) for stateful, multi-turn coaching conversations.
Advise, help build, and orchestrate data pipelines that unify fragmented workplace data (surveys, goals, performance reviews, feedback, 1-1 notes) into coherent coaching context
Translate customer requirements into technical solutions - working backwards from user needs to system design. Creating technical documentation to support literacy, technical transfer and engineering practice.
Partner closely with product, design, and people science to ensure the features developed are fit for purpose, and in-line with the existing product expectations to ensure seamless partnership transfer of technology.
Contribute to evaluation frameworks and bias testing to meet enterprise requirements for transparency and fairness
Build cutting-edge, working prototypes, integrated into our environments which validate new approaches and accelerate learning.
What we're looking for


Must Haves:

Proven commercial experience taking ML/AI systems to production.
Strong technical writer and communicator
Full stack software development experience, ideally Python, React, PGVector
Strong software engineering fundamentals - you write clean, tested, maintainable code. 
You leverage Software development AI tooling effectively.
Experience with LLM application development (prompt and context engineering, RAG, agent architectures)
Hands-on experience designing and integrating data pipelines - you're comfortable moving data across systems, working within rigorous security standards, handling messy real-world inputs, and building robust orchestration
A pragmatic, solution-focused mindset - you evaluate new technology through the lens of "does this scalably solve the problem?" not "is this technically interesting?"
You fit our values with the proactivity to take risks, and the humility to learn in public. You take pride in your work and its successful utilisation, stability, extendability and maintainability. 

Strong signals:

Experience at startups or founding teams - comfortable with ambiguity and fast iteration
Postgraduate degree (Masters or PhD) in Machine Learning, Computer Science, Applied Mathematics, or related quantitative field
Evidence of taking cutting-edge (relevant) techniques from paper to production
Experience with evaluation/benchmarking frameworks for AI systems
Experience integrating scalable solutions such as advanced Speech-to-Text (STT) and Text-to-Speech (TTS) pipelines (e.g., Whisper, ElevenLabs) with streaming capabilities
Experience implementing GraphRAG or Knowledge Graphs (e.g., Neo4j)

Bonus:

Familiarity with people analytics, HR tech, or behavioral science applications
Contributions to data ethics, algorithmic fairness, or responsible AI initiatives
Open source contributions or public technical writing
Why join AIRX


You'll work at scale on hard problems that matter - building AI that helps organizations develop their people, improve feedback culture, and foster the conditions for sustainable high performance. Our approach is deeply informed by Culture Amp's people science research. You'll be surrounded by talented and passionate advocates for humanity and cutting edge AI in the world of work.

We believe that our employees are the heartbeat of our success. We're committed to fostering a work environment that truly cares for and develops its people, and creates lasting positive impact. In addition to providing a competitive compensation package, some of the key benefits we offer are: 

Employee Share Options Program: We empower you to be an owner in Culture Amp and share in our success
Programs, coaching, and budgets to help you thrive personally and professionally
Access to external providers for mental wellbeing and coaching support to sustain the wellbeing, safety and development of our people
Monthly Camper Life Allowance: An automatic allowance paid out each month with your pay - you can spend it however you like to help improve your experience and life outside work
Team budgets dedicated to team building activities and connection
Intentional quarterly wellbeing pauses: A quarterly company-wide shutdown day in each region to to collectively pause, reset and focus on restoration and rest, without having to tap into individual vacation time
Extended year-end breaks: An extended refresh period at the end of year
Excellent parental leave and in work support program available from day 1 of joining Culture Amp
5 Social Impact Days a year to make a positive impact on the community outside of work
MacBooks for you to do your best & a work from home office budget to spend on setting up your home office
Medical insurance coverage for you and your family (Available for US & UK only) 

Additionally, we don't just focus on our internal community; we believe in creating a better world of work for all. We're committed to diversity, equity, and inclusion, with Employee Resource Groups and ally communities in place. 

We have a strong commitment to Anti-Racism, and endeavor to lead by example. Every step we make as a business towards anti-racism is another step we can take to support our customers in making a better world (of work). You can see our current commitments to Anti-Racism here.

2 years max term fulltime opportunity (with view to extend)
Flexible location across NSW, WA, VIC and TAS, with the option to work in a hybrid model
Contribute to high‑quality project delivery across a diverse and growing organisation

About the Role:

As a Business Analyst, you will work with stakeholders from all parts of BaptistCare to elicit requirements and capture business needs, to articulate and document business requirements, to conduct as-is/to-be business process mapping and business process design, to participate in project delivery through design reviews and walk-throughs, to validate and communicate outcomes.

You’ll play a pivotal role in transforming aged care through technology by supporting the selection and rollout of our new national clinical records platform across all 51 aged care homes. You’ll assess existing clinical systems, conduct market scans for alternative solutions, and evaluate applications to identify the best platform for BaptistCare. Beyond selection, you’ll be instrumental in supporting the implementation of the chosen solution, ensuring smooth integration into daily operations and delivering tangible benefits for both residents and staff. This is a unique opportunity to apply your analytical expertise, process insight, and passion for improving clinical care through innovative technology.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead structured analysis and documentation to support the selection and implementation of a national clinical records platform, reducing the risk of vendor or configuration issues.
Facilitate stakeholder engagement, capturing clinical and operational requirements, workflows, and concerns to ensure all perspectives are reflected in evaluation and design decisions.
Conduct detailed gap analysis of current clinical systems to define must-have features, ensuring the new solution meets both operational and clinical needs.
Develop evaluation criteria and assessment metrics, providing objective, transparent comparison of vendor solutions.
Analyse and document all cost components, highlighting variances and providing insights to support informed financial decision-making.
Support transition and implementation planning, clarifying priorities, sequencing, and dependencies to ensure smooth adoption across all 51 aged care homes.
Translate complex processes and data into clear, actionable insights to guide strategic decisions and optimise clinical operations.

About the Team:

The Information & Digital team drives innovation and transforms care at BaptistCare through cutting-edge technology, seamless operations, and smart risk management. You’ll join a collaborative, solutions-focused team that values creativity, flexibility, and turning complex projects into real-world impact for our frontline teams.

Minimum 5 years’ experience as a business analyst delivering complex process, data and system change initiatives.
Previous experience within healthcare and/or aged care sector or consultancy experience
Demonstrated experience working on enterprise system implementations or replacements, particularly clinical systems e.g.: (EHR, EMR solutions).
Tertiary qualification in Business, Information Technology, Business Analysis or a related discipline.
Experience in mapping, analysing, and improving business processes using BPMN or other structured process methodologies.
Solid understanding of systems, data and integration concepts, with the ability to document application and data architectures.
Experience defining and supporting data and system migration approaches, including sequencing, dependencies and risk considerations.
High-level written and verbal communication skills, with the ability to translate complex concepts for executives, business users and technical team
Previous experience participating on Project teams
Experience using business analysis and delivery tools such as Visio, Jira, Confluence, MS Project or equivalent.
Ability to develop relationships with key organisational stakeholders, including Execs and Business users.
Highly developed interpersonal skills and ability to work harmoniously in a team environment.

We are proud to be part of the merged care organisation that will be known nationally as BaptistCare. As a for purpose, Christian care organisation, we are committed to providing exceptional support and services across Australia.  Together with Baptcare (VIC, TAS, SA) and Baptist Care SA we employ over 12,000 dedicated employees and support over 38,000 customers to help people live well with dignity and purpose. From older Australians and their families to people facing significant disadvantage, our passion and our priority are the customers we serve. We strive to deliver care as it should be – with people right at the centre. 

We love what we do and the communities we help. With us you can deliver life transforming care, create a career you’ll love, and join a team who make a difference.
